  "prompt": "What is one life hack so important you know that most of the people are unaware?",
  "response": "One highly impactful life hack that many people overlook is the **\"Two-Minute Rule\"** for productivity and habit formation. Here's how it works:\n\n### **Two-Minute Rule:**  \nIf a task takes less than two minutes to complete, do it **immediately** instead of postponing it.  \n\n### Why It Works:\n1. **Prevents Procrastination:** Small tasks often pile up and create mental clutter. By addressing them right away, you avoid the stress of accumulating \"to-dos.\"  \n2. **Builds Momentum:** Completing quick tasks gives you a sense of accomplishment, which can motivate you to tackle larger tasks.  \n3. **Reduces Decision Fatigue:** By removing the need to decide when to do small tasks, you free up mental energy for more important decisions.  \n\n### Examples:\n- Reply to a quick email.  \n- Put away a piece of clothing instead of leaving it on the chair.  \n- Wash a dish right after using it.  \n- Write down a reminder or idea before you forget it.  \n\n### Bonus Tip:  \nFor larger tasks, use the **\"Two-Minute Starting Rule\"**\u2014commit to working on it for just two minutes. Often, starting is the hardest part, and once you begin, you\u2019ll likely continue.  \n\nThis simple rule can transform your productivity and help you maintain a clutter-free mind and environment. Try it consistently for a week, and you\u2019ll notice a big difference!",
